  "method": "Per target: codeweb --dependents was reconciled against an INDEPENDENT exhaustive grep+read of the corpus (one thorough pass per target), then hand-adjudicated. Truth = real reference sites by NATURAL attribution, independent of codeweb's graph coverage (a real site in a file codeweb failed to index is still truth, so coverage gaps count honestly).",
  "attributionRule": "id = `<relative-path>:<enclosing-named-symbol>`; module-scope refs (imports, top-level re-exports, module-scope code) and refs inside anonymous it()/describe()/callback bodies use `<file>:<module>`. Usages inside a named function/method use that name. Dedupe: many refs in one enclosing symbol collapse to ONE id. The target's own declaration line is NOT a caller; its module-scope self-uses (recursion via an enclosing named fn, re-export, static setup) ARE.",
