    "primary": "FILE-LEVEL recall/precision (collapse every id to its file). This is robust to the attribution-convention mismatch below and answers the real refactor question: which FILES must I open and edit. Lead with this + the (oracle-free) step delta.",
    "secondary": "SYMBOL-LEVEL recall/precision against the ids here. Conservative and HONEST but attribution-noisy: codeweb attributes a file's import / test-callback ref to an enclosing NAMED function (createInstance, makeResponse, ...) while this set uses `<file>:<module>` per the rule, so codeweb is dinged at symbol level even when it found the right file. Report it, but do not lead with it.",
    "scopePartition": "Also grade truth INTERSECTED with the files codeweb actually indexed (derivable from the graph). The in-indexed-scope number isolates discovery quality from coverage gaps; the full-repo number includes coverage gaps (e.g. unindexed .ts/smoke fixtures, merge.test.js). Report both; the gap is itself an honest finding.",
    "variants": "external = drop ids whose file == the target's own definition file. Computed mechanically by the regrade/harness; shows the result is not driven by self-references."
  },
